    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:60px;"><anchor id="2DCAM-DIALOG-CAMLIFEFACTORS" styleclass="Body Text"><keywords><keyword>2D-Cam dialog<keyword>Cam-Life-: Allow Pitting:?</keyword></keyword></keywords></anchor><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" figurelistinclude="0"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif" styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><caption><![CDATA[Enable Pitting Factor]]></caption><title>Click to exapand /collapse</title></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Allow Pitting to ~15% of Cam Surface</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="VariableName">Steels and Cast-Irons of Categories 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 9, 10, and 11</text> (See<text styleclass="Body Text"> Cam Life Results below</text>) </para>
                <para styleclass="Body Table">These categories allow a small amount of surface pitting to occur, at which time the pitting stabilizes. This is called non-progressive pitting.</para>
                <para styleclass="Body Table">If you allow up to ~15% pitting, the cam-life is extended. </para>
                <para styleclass="Body Table">In <text styleclass="VariableName">mission-critical</text> applications, for example <text styleclass="VariableName">manned flight</text> - you would <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">not</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Allow Pitting</text>.</para>
                <para styleclass="Body Table">Also, if this is a new and important application, then I would not <text styleclass="VariableName">Allow Pitting</text>.</para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:60px;"><anchor id="2DCAM-DIALOG-CAMLIFE-MATERIAL" styleclass="Body Text"><keywords><keyword>2D-Cam dialog<keyword>Cam Life - Cam Material and Hardness</keyword></keyword></keywords></anchor><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Separator-Header" figurelistinclude="0"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif" styleclass="Separator-Header"><caption><![CDATA[ Cam Material and Hardness ]]></caption><title>Click to exapand /collapse</title></toggle></para>
